                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a lively and energetic 4-year-old boy who attends a local preschool, where he loves painting, building blocks, and chasing his classmates on the playground. He lives at home with both parents and a 7-year-old sister in a cozy suburban neighborhood. He enjoys watching animated cartoons, playing with toy cars, and helping his mother water the plants in the backyard garden. {patientName} has a cheerful disposition but today appears visibly uncomfortable — he is brought in by his mother, who reports he has been coughing persistently for the past five days.\n\nOn presentation, {patientName} is alert but mildly irritable, sitting on his mother's lap and occasionally burying his face in her shoulder. He has a low-grade fever with flushed cheeks and mild nasal congestion. His cough is wet and productive, and he has had several episodes of coughing fits that have disturbed his sleep. His appetite has been slightly reduced, and he has been drinking fewer fluids than usual. He does not appear to be in severe respiratory distress, but his breathing is slightly faster than normal.\n\n{patientName}'s mother mentions that several children in his preschool class had similar cold-like symptoms about a week ago. The household is non-smoking. His father occasionally works from home as a software developer, and his mother is a primary school teacher. The family has a small dog at home, though there are no known animal-related symptoms. {patientName} is generally an active, healthy child who rarely misses playtime outdoors, rain or shine.\n\n{patientName}'s parents are attentive and concerned. His mother is particularly worried because the cough has worsened at night, and he once vomited after a severe coughing episode. She denies any choking events, foreign body aspiration, or recent travel. The family follows a balanced diet with fruits and vegetables, and {patientName} drinks milk and water regularly."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
