        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} was born at 39 weeks via normal vaginal delivery with no neonatal complications. He has met all developmental milestones appropriate for his age. His immunization schedule is up to date, including influenza vaccine received last autumn. He has had two prior episodes of upper respiratory tract infections in the last 12 months, both managed conservatively at home.\n\n{patientName} has no known history of asthma, atopic dermatitis, or recurrent wheezing. He has never been hospitalized. His diet is well-balanced, and his growth parameters are within normal range for his age. He attends preschool five days a week, which increases his exposure to common respiratory viral pathogens. There is no history of passive smoke exposure in the household. The family has a dog but no known environmental sensitivities have been documented. No recent travel history outside the country."
          }
        ]
